				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">SBC is more like add carry and one's complement of operand to A. Thus you set carry to have it add two's complement to A (and clear carry to do a borrow). It's all so elegant.<br /><br />BTW, a way of intuitively grasping negation is that you first flip all the bits, which is equivalent to subtracting the value from $FF. But you want it subtracted from $100, which is one more, so you add one.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

